{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_015qbxAXSek9Ca6y5kp8CTbv","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The frontend code in `openDrawer` (line 274) makes a fetch call to the API endpoint. The handler `handleAPIStepContent` reads the file content. Let me trace through the issue more carefully.\n\nLooking at the `handleAPIStepContent` handler (line 1143), it reads the step config's `prompt` field. But looking at `handleAPIWorkflows` (line 1058), the config values have the `file(\"...\")` syntax stripped:\n\n```go\nif strings.HasPrefix(v, `file(\"`) && strings.HasSuffix(v, `\")`) {\n    cleanConfig[k] = v[6 : len(v)-2]\n\n\n```\n\nSo the frontend sees the clean path (e.g., `.cloche/prompts/fix.md`), which is correct.\n\nNow in `handleAPIStepContent`, I'm checking if the step config has a prompt field and handling both the cleaned path format and the raw DSL syntax with the `file(\"...\")` wrapper...\n\nReading the file from disk...\n\nBut the issue mentions it shows the filename without loading the contents, so something's going wrong in the API call. Let me trace back through the DSL parser to see what values actually end up in the step config.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5511,"cache_read_input_tokens":34253,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":5511,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"36334803-23cc-465d-b4ed-5517c3e5b5e4","uuid":"46da0770-82b9-4d7c-876c-a9e5e374c0dd"}
